text: Hein-Arne Mathiesen (born 4 April 1971) is a retired Norwegian ski jumper. In the World Cup he finished once among the top 10, with a ninth place from Willingen in February 1997. He won the Continental Cup in the 1996/97 season. ==External links== * Category:1971 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian male ski jumpers
